# ATT&CK — BTLO Challenge
**Date:** 20 May 2026
**Platform:** Blue Team Labs Online
**Category:** Incident Response
**Difficulty:** Easy
**Points:** 10

## What was the scenario?
Identify threats and attacks from 5 scenarios from MITRE ATT&CK framework and how to solve them 

## Tools I used
*MITRE ATT&CK SITE 
*OSINT

## What I found
* T1538 cloud discovery technique that doesn't use an API — turned out to be T1538 (attackers logging into Azure dashboard with stolen credentials and clicking around)
* Identified a real APT group Blind Eagle/APT-C-36 just from a suspicious port number 4050 in a log
* LockerGoga is a software that locks you out of your own system during a ransomware attack.
* Pass the Hash - attacker steals your password hash and uses it without ever knowing your actual password. Had to OSINT it from old community writeups

## What was tricky
* MITRE ATT&CK framework is more of a living document and get updated so finding the 
 technique ID was difficult for some. had to google to find the old one. Meaning i may have 
to google sometimes. 

## What I learned
*In looking for matching IDs in the MITRE ATT&CK Frame work, there are 8 main ATT&CK Object Types and 
the naming of the ID tend to show this:
TA = Tactic
T = Technique
M = Mitigation
G = Group
S = Software
C = Campaign
* There are Sub-techniques of Techniques - more like specific 
variations and usually have ".000" (numbers inclusive) like this T1566.001.

## MITRE ATT&CK
- T1538 — Cloud Service Dashboard
- G0099 — APT-C-36 / Blind Eagle
- TA0001 — Initial Access
- S0372 — LockerGoga
- T1550.002 — Pass the Hash
